You're trying to sound tough, but I know the truth, boy.

247
00:16:03,681 --> 00:16:07,460
The real terror of all this is
starting to sink in to your thick skull.

248
00:16:07,539 --> 00:16:09,394
I can even tell what you're thinking.

249
00:16:09,682 --> 00:16:11,802
"How long can he stay underwater?

250
00:16:11,968 --> 00:16:16,163
"I can probably last about two
minutes, but can he last longer than me?"

251
00:16:16,287 --> 00:16:17,705
Am I right, brother?

252
00:16:18,976 --> 00:16:20,224
Let me answer you.

253
00:16:20,460 --> 00:16:24,522
My lung capacity is three times that of a normal human's.

254
00:16:25,313 --> 00:16:27,111
See, for years, I've been training.

255
00:16:27,416 --> 00:16:30,750
Six minutes and 12 seconds is my best submerged time.

256
00:16:30,853 --> 00:16:34,317
You must be dizzy just hearing
that number, right, brother?

257
00:16:34,590 --> 00:16:35,353
And...

258
00:16:37,742 --> 00:16:43,725
Dark Blue Moon's fins are cutters that move
faster than a ship's propeller, far sharper, too.

259
00:16:44,121 --> 00:16:48,906
Before you get overconfident again, you
might wanna take a good, hard look at your stand.

260
00:16:49,351 --> 00:16:54,354
Seems Dark Blue Moon's barnacles have
taken a liking to absorbing your stand's power.

261
00:16:54,860 --> 00:16:59,440
How does it feel to have your life
energy slowly draining away from your body?

262
00:17:02,182 --> 00:17:04,469
Trying to run away by swimming back up?

263
00:17:04,785 --> 00:17:06,432
Take a good look around you.

264
00:17:08,012 --> 00:17:09,761
Haven't you realized, brother,

265
00:17:09,913 --> 00:17:12,979
Dark Blue Moon has created an underwater whirlpool?

266
00:17:13,107 --> 00:17:15,599
There's no way you can possibly escape.

267
00:17:15,894 --> 00:17:17,404
That's right. Swim faster.

268
00:17:17,647 --> 00:17:21,127
You'll just make it harder to
breathe while your power keeps draining.

269
00:17:21,483 --> 00:17:26,406
But it's little too early to kill a
stupid, smartass punk like you just yet.

270
00:17:27,220 --> 00:17:29,988
It's been too long! He's still not coming up!

271
00:17:30,237 --> 00:17:32,926
A giant whirlpool! It must have him trapped.

272
00:17:34,888 --> 00:17:36,206
Where the hell is JoJo?

273
00:17:36,459 --> 00:17:37,668
Let's go and save him.

274
00:17:44,005 --> 00:17:45,277
These are scales.

275
00:17:45,696 --> 00:17:48,492
That guy's stand has scales as sharp as razors.

276
00:17:48,823 --> 00:17:51,407
There are countless scales swirling in that whirlpool.

277
00:17:51,490 --> 00:17:54,663
He wasn't bluffing when he said he
could beat all five of us at once.

278
00:17:55,029 --> 00:17:57,182
It's like a watery ant-lion pit.

279
00:17:58,013 --> 00:18:01,345
If we dive in, it's very
possible we'll be sliced to pieces.

280
00:18:03,626 --> 00:18:04,812
His scales?

281
00:18:10,082 --> 00:18:12,082
I'll take another guess at what you're thinking.

282
00:18:12,372 --> 00:18:15,636
"In a whirlpool, only one spot stays still."

283
00:18:17,170 --> 00:18:18,581
Such mundane logic.

284
00:18:18,916 --> 00:18:19,955
"It's the eye.

285
00:18:20,090 --> 00:18:23,226
If I jump into the center where he is, I can attack him."

286
00:18:24,566 --> 00:18:25,942
That's what you're thinking, right?

287
00:18:26,423 --> 00:18:29,732
If you believe you can hit me
with that punch of yours again,

288
00:18:30,081 --> 00:18:31,870
then come and give it a shot.

289
00:18:32,094 --> 00:18:36,763
Throw your worthless stand at me. It's
power's so drained, it doesn't have a chance.

290
00:18:37,070 --> 00:18:41,816
See if you can manage an attack, one that's
even sharper than these underwater cutters.

291
00:18:41,947 --> 00:18:43,613
I'm waiting, brother.

292
00:18:45,744 --> 00:18:48,713
Damn him! We're completely helpless.

293
00:18:49,065 --> 00:18:49,874
It's JoJo!

294
00:18:50,819 --> 00:18:52,942
I just saw JoJo in the whirlpool.

295
00:18:53,851 --> 00:18:55,653
I don't think he's moving down there.

296
00:18:55,980 --> 00:18:57,144
So he went limp?

297
00:18:57,353 --> 00:18:59,582
He wasn't struggling against the whirlpool?

298
00:19:00,004 --> 00:19:03,340
Well, that might actually be a good thing.

299
00:19:04,919 --> 00:19:08,432
Weren't you gonna turn me into sashimi, boy?

300
00:19:10,507 --> 00:19:13,000
You're the one who's gonna be sliced up.

301
00:19:19,959 --> 00:19:22,420
Star finger!

302
00:19:28,412 --> 00:19:30,201
Sorry. Did I interrupt you?

303
00:19:30,556 --> 00:19:32,010
Who's gonna be sashimi?

304
00:19:35,120 --> 00:19:37,427
What's that? I can't hear you.

305
00:19:37,678 --> 00:19:40,731
You're gonna have to speak up. We're underwater.

306
00:19:41,098 --> 00:19:43,066
But your power was being drained.

307
00:19:43,233 --> 00:19:46,208
You let yourself go limp on purpose, didn't you?

308
00:19:46,233 --> 00:19:48,384
You concentrated your power in your fingers.

309
00:19:48,409 --> 00:19:51,213
Th-that's what you were thinking all along.

310
00:19:52,269 --> 00:19:53,670
Not even close.

311
00:19:54,269 --> 00:19:58,848
The only thing on my mind is how gross it'll be

312
00:19:58,907 --> 00:20:03,167
when I kick your stupid ass and you
piss yourself underwater, and that's all.

313
00:20:04,106 --> 00:20:05,108
Bye, pops.

314
00:20:13,890 --> 00:20:14,469
JoJo!

315
00:20:14,558 --> 00:20:16,347
That's my grandson for you.

316
00:20:18,326 --> 00:20:19,770
Well done, Jotaro.

317
00:20:20,271 --> 00:20:21,644
Hurry and come u... huh?

318
00:20:21,779 --> 00:20:22,080
Huh?

319
00:20:28,754 --> 00:20:32,533
Th-that captain planted some bombs after all! Damn it!

320
00:20:33,754 --> 00:20:35,549
Send out a distress call!

321
00:21:09,418 --> 00:21:11,059
Here. You should have some water.

322
00:21:11,484 --> 00:21:15,535
We've sent out distress calls, so someone
should be here with a rescue ship soon enough.

323
00:21:17,662 --> 00:21:19,835
Okay, just what the hell is going on here?

324
00:21:20,178 --> 00:21:22,629
I don't get any of this. Who are you guys?

325
00:21:23,007 --> 00:21:25,623
Just think of us as fellow travelers.

326
00:21:26,117 --> 00:21:28,109
You're on a journey to see your father,

327
00:21:28,855 --> 00:21:30,964
while I'm on one for my daughter.

328
00:21:31,374 --> 00:21:31,675
Heh.

329
00:21:37,127 --> 00:21:39,369
Hey, that's the only fresh water we have,

330
00:21:39,544 --> 00:21:41,045
so don't spit it out. We need it.

331
00:21:41,070 --> 00:21:41,849
N-N-No.

332
00:21:45,517 --> 00:21:47,261
Everyone, look there!

333
00:21:47,393 --> 00:21:47,845
Hmm?

334
00:21:49,123 --> 00:21:49,655
Huh?

335
00:22:13,301 --> 00:22:15,670
All the old paintings on the tomb

336
00:22:15,695 --> 00:22:17,838
They do the sand dance, don't you know

337
00:22:17,863 --> 00:22:19,182
If they move too quick

338
00:22:19,207 --> 00:22:20,318
Oh, whey, oh

339
00:22:20,343 --> 00:22:22,636
They're falling down like a domino

340
00:22:22,661 --> 00:22:25,004
All the bazaar men by the Nile

341
00:22:25,029 --> 00:22:27,259
They got the money on a bet

342
00:22:27,284 --> 00:22:28,705
Gold crocodiles

343
00:22:28,730 --> 00:22:29,621
Oh, whey, oh

344
00:22:29,646 --> 00:22:31,900
They snap their teeth on your cigarette

345
00:22:31,925 --> 00:22:34,175
Foreign types with the hookah pipes say

346
00:22:34,200 --> 00:22:36,558
Whey, oh, whey, oh

347
00:22:36,583 --> 00:22:40,095
Ay, whey, oh, whey, oh

